Package jkhet

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Controller
    Controller class that launches the GUI or runs the command-line interface
    Djed
    Class for the Djed piece, a double-mirrored board piece that can swap locations with adjacent pieces.
    Gui
    Class controlling all interface requirements of the game.
    Obelisk
    Class for Obelisks, which contain no mirrored sides but can take two laser hits before dying.
    Params
    Generic board parameters.
    Pharaoh
    Class for the Pharaoh, which has no mirrored sides; if a player loses their Pharaoh, the game is over.
    Piece
    Master abstract class for board pieces.
    Pyramid
    Class for Pyramids, pieces with one mirrored side; can reflect lasers, rotate, or move into any adjacent, legal, unoccupied space.
